According to the 2010 census, there were 1,117 people living in Plano. The population density was 417.9 inhabitants/km<sup>2</sup>. Of the 1,117 people, Plano was composed of 94.09% White, 3.04% [[African American]], 0% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0.9% [[Asian people|Asian]], 0% [[Pacific Islander]], 0.81% were other races, and 1.16% of two or more races. 1.61% are [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic]] or [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Latino]] of any race.

